Docs.summary: Gets or sets the roll-up type for a custom field.

example.para: The following example uses CustomFieldWS as the name of a web reference to the Custom Fields web service (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_vti_bin/psi/CustomFields.asmx). remarks.para: A lookup table leaf node has no subordinate nodes.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool MD_PROP_IS_MULTILINE_TEXT { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.MD_PROP_IS_MULTILINE_TEXT : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the text custom field can contain multiple lines.
Docs.value: True if the field can contain multiple lines; otherwise, False.

remarks.para: A multiline text custom field can contain up to 4000 bytes. Multiline text custom fields are for use in project detail pages (PDPs) and with workflows in Project Web App for demand management. Multiline text custom fields are not usable in Project Professional.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool MD_PROP_IS_REQUIRED { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.MD_PROP_IS_REQUIRED : bool with get, set

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool MD_PROP_IS_WORKFLOW_CONTROLLED { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.MD_PROP_IS_WORKFLOW_CONTROLLED : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the custom field is controlled by a workflow.
Docs.value: True if controlled by a workflow; otherwise, False.

remarks.para: Caution: The CreateCustomFields, CreateCustomFields2, UpdateCustomFields, and UpdateCustomFields2 methods, as well as Project Web App, all allow you to create an enterprise project custom field of type Flag, and set the custom field to be workflow controlled. However, Project Server workflows cannot control Flag custom fields. You should not set MD_PROP_IS_WORKFLOW_CONTROLLED to True for project custom fields of type Flag.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property int MD_PROP_MAX_VALUES { int get(); void set(int value); };
member this.MD_PROP_MAX_VALUES : int with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the custom field has a single value or uses a multivalue lookup table.
Docs.value: An integer that determines the size of a lookup table.

remarks.para: Set MD_PROP_MAX_VALUES with the enumeration. Single-value custom fields are set to DEFAULT or ONE. A multivalue custom field uses a lookup table and MD_PROP_MAX_VALUES must be set to TWOHUNDREDFIFTY; that is, a multivalue custom field can have a maximum of 250 values in a lookup table.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Byte MD_PROP_TYPE_ENUM { System::Byte get(); void set(System::Byte value); };
member this.MD_PROP_TYPE_ENUM : byte with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the type of the custom field.
Docs.value: A custom field type.

remarks.para: can be one of the following custom field types: COST, DATE, DURATION, FLAG, NUMBER, or TEXT. Only a custom field of type TEXT can have a hierarchical lookup table. A custom field of type FLAG cannot use a lookup table. Set with the enumeration.

example.para: The following example uses CustomFieldWS as the name of a web reference to the Custom Fields web service (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_vti_bin/psi/CustomFields.asmx). The btnCustomField_Click event handler is for a button on a Windows form application, such as LoginDemo in the Project SDK download.
